INSTALL file for mlogind

0. Prerequisites:
 - cmake
 - X.org or XFree86
 - libxmu
 - libpng
 - libjpeg

1. To build and install the program:
 - mkdir build ; cd build
 - cmake .. [options]
   Common options:
   -DUSE_PAM=yes          Enable PAM support
   -DUSE_CONSOLEKIT=yes   Enable CONSOLEKIT support
   -DUSE_RSVG=yes         Enable SVG support via librsvg
   -DBUILD_MLOGINLOCK=yes Build mloginlock (requires PAM)
   -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON Build shared libraries (default: ON)
 - cmake --build .
 - sudo cmake --install .
 
2. automatic startup
Edit the init scripts according to your OS/Distribution.
